  options:
  - optionText: "What\u2019s your husband\u2019s work?"
    replyText: Oh, Caleb? He works in the cornfield right next to our house. Then
      he sells the corn to Pinehill, where they process it into flour. It keeps him
      busy most of the day!
    nextNode: 0
    exitOption: 0
    conditionType: 0
    questID: 0
    objectID: 0
    amountObject: 0
    actions: []
  - optionText: How do you like living in Evergreen City?
    replyText: "I can\u2019t complain\u2026 Although I spend most of my days cleaning
      and cooking for my husband."
    nextNode: 0
    exitOption: 0
    conditionType: 0
    questID: 0
    objectID: 0
    amountObject: 0
    actions: []
  - optionText: Can I help you with something?
    replyText: "Well\u2026 actually, yes. The nuclear battery in my stove has run
      out, and I have no idea where to find a new one. If you manage to find a working
      one, bring it to me. I\u2019ll reward you well."
    nextNode: 0
    exitOption: 0
    conditionType: 1
    questID: 44
    objectID: 0
    amountObject: 0
    actions:
    - {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6fc7bb42dace2a149a0debb389c2b257, type: 2}
  - optionText: Where am I supposed to get a battery like that? I doubt anyone even
      makes them anymore.
    replyText: "To be honest\u2026 I\u2019m not sure. Maybe in an unexploded nuclear
      bomb\u2026 or from a wandering trader."
    nextNode: 0
